This paper discusses the analysis of evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the comparison of natural and artificial evolution, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses analytical theory to analyze the runtime, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
